<h4 id="dealing-with-rain">Dealing with Rain:</h4>

<p>This might seem like a silly talking point, but it’s something I’ve been harshly reminded of this weekend. After an unusually long summer in 2015, the fall of 2016 here in the Southeast U.S. has unusually (and wonderfully) 
cool and dry.</p>

<p>Now, that has come with some problems (e.g. wild fires and 
consequent fire bans in nearly all North Georgia / 
Tennessee camping areas), but it has meant early prime 
climbing conditions.</p>

<p>At any rate this past weekend has brought much needed rain and conditions 
more typical of early winter in Georgia.  Which means utterly disgusting 
camping conditions to the cadence of 40’ and constant drizzling rain. Yuck!</p>

<p>The weather spoiled me early on, but now I’m reminded how winter is going 
to bring it’s own set of difficulties compared to summer.</p>

